#, no-wrap
msgid "Modify NetworkManager connection profile autoconnect property"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:11
msgid "First use nmcli to query and display the current value of the autoconnect property for all network connections on a Rocky Linux system. Type:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "nmcli -f name,autoconnect connection \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:18
msgid "To change the value of a property for a network connection use the `modify` sub-command with `nmcli connection`.  For example, to change the autoconnect property value from `no` to `yes` for the `ens3` connection profile, type:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo nmcli con mod ens3 connection.autoconnect yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commands Explained"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "connection (con)       : NetworkManager connection object. \n"
"modify (mod)           : Modify one or more properties of a given connection profile.\n"
"connection.autoconnect : The setting and property (<setting>.<property>)\n"
"-f, --fields           : specify fields to output.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/nmcli.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "This tip shows how to modify an existing NetworkManager connection profile. This is useful when the network interface does not automatically get activated after a fresh Rocky Linux installation or system update. \n"
"The reason for this is often because the value of autoconnect property is set to `no`. You can use the `nmcli` command to quickly change the value to `yes`.  \n"
msgstr ""

